Ok, so normally I don’t like eating out. Too many years spent working in restaurants. But this place gets my full backing. The head chef is nice. They're clean there. They washed their hands in front of me and changed gloves. I ordered beef ribs, rice, mac and cheese, and corn bread. The rice was good . The mac and cheese was completely flawless it had to have been 5 kinds of cheese. To be honest it could be considered a meal all to itself. The ribs. I'm a little torn about. The meat is tender and delicious,  but I guess I just  expected the serving to have more. But then again I do eat a lot. It was 1 long bone with about 5 cut pieces of meat falling off it. The chef gave me extra sauce to mix in the rice. Which is what I usually do. The cornbread came with fried onions to put on the ribs. He kept all the dry stuff together. The cornbread was slightly sweet and it doesn’t crumble. This was just a few things on the menu. To me it’s enough to keep me coming back. The chef also gave me tea to help with my immune system. Hospitality like that is what turns customers into clients.

Alright, here’s my honest opinion. They have really good food, for sure. I’m in love with their amarillo burger, husband loves their juicy Lucy and steaks. However, they’re not very consistent with their food/service. Sometimes we’ll be served chips and salsa while we wait for our food, other times not. I’ve ordered the Amarillo burger 3 times (it’s good okay) but each time there was something different. The first time I was given an onion ring with my burger and sautéed onions inside- 10/10, it was absolutely perfect. The next time, no onion ring and instead of sautéed onions I got crunchy onions in the burger? Still not bad though. Then the last time was just...strange. There were regular raw onions, pickles, and the bun was even different. I mean I still enjoyed it because the Amarillo sauce is what makes the burger, but I was disappointed in the lack of consistency in the restaurant. Also the fries are always over cooked. I still get excited going there because I really do enjoy their food, the environment’s nice, and the people are friendly. Just wish they were more consistent.

Addys BBQ:  This ended up being a last minute spot. Neither of us had any intention to go here but we were looking for something close by and not too expensive with great food. We looked at the photos on Yelp and the fact that it was Halal and we were sold. So we headed over and as you walk in you notice how amazing the decor is. I absolutely loved the atmosphere of the place. The wait staff is cordial and the food was absolutely amazing.  For starters we got a side of Mac n cheese, masala fries and jerk wings. The Mac n cheese was the best Mac n cheese I have ever had in my life.The only thing I think they can add is to have a variation with lobster Mac n cheese. Other than that it was perfect; right temperature right cheese consistency our entire table loved it. The wings were nothing special, they were good wings but you can only expect jerk wings to get so close to perfection if they are not from an authentic jerk spot. Lastly the Masala fries were told to be spicy but they had more of a subtle spice to it, almost similar to Cajun fries, which we loved nonetheless.  For the main courses we got filet mignon, rib eye, beef ribs and a Cajun chicken sandwich. Both the filet mignon and the rib eye came with a side of potatoes with gravy and grilled vegetables and both steaks were cooked as ordered which is sometimes tough in certain restaurants. My other friends who ordered the Cajun chicken sandwich and the beef ribs enjoyed their entrees very much and you can imagine especially since they look so good !  The only thing I would want them to improve on is their wait staff. It’s something very small but small detail can make or break a business. We had asked our waiter to allow us time to finish our starters before bringing out that main courses which is exactly what he didn’t do. So as we were eating we were trying to scramble and make room on the table for the food and rush and eat the starters so the main course doesn’t get cold... which is exactly what I was afraid of. Eventually we didn’t have room so we used the table next to us to place some of the courses and dishes.  Lastly we asked for some of our food to be packaged to go, instead of taking our food to the kitchen to package the wait staff gave us the bins to package ourself. I normally wouldn’t bother commenting on this but since the food was so good I expected that extra level of service as well.  There menu has so many delicious items that you can’t possibly try them in one visit, I will definitely be back with company sooner than later.  Food: 5/5 Service: 3/5  Addys BBQ: 8/10 $100.70 bill total.
